com.jmr.wrapper.common.complex

Class ComplexPiece

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jmr.wrapper.common.complex.ComplexPiece

  • public class ComplexPiece
extends java.lang.Object
    Networking Library ComplexPiece.java Purpose: A piece of a object's byte array that corresponds to a complex object. This piece's data is sent over a socket and recreated into an object later on.
    Version:
    1.0 7/25/2014
    Author:
    Jon R (Baseball435)

      • getByteArray

        private byte[] getByteArray(byte[] data)
        Takes the id, converts it to four bytes and adds it in front of the bytes of data. It also makes the first index in the array equal to 99 because that is the key that will be used on the client/server side to determine whether or not it is part of a complex object.
        Parameters:
        data - The object's byte array.
        Returns:
        The combined array.

      • addArrays

        private byte[] addArrays(byte[] array,
               byte[] checksumBytes)
        Takes the byte array of the object and id and puts the 10 bytes of the checksum in front of it.
        Parameters:
        array - The array to put the checksum in front of.
        checksumBytes - The checksum value in bytes.
        Returns:
        The combined array.
